Defendant Ian G Magolan in court, in custody, with attorney Katie Kegel.    Melissa Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Zilavy motions the Court for discharge of the Defendant from Alcohol Treatment Court.  Attorney Bricco provides a statement to the Court.  The Defendant provides a statement and requests he be allowed to continue with Alcohol Treatment Court.   The Court schedules the case for a discharge hearing on Thursday, June 15, 2017 during Alcohol Treatment Court.  Attorney Kegel to provide written documentation with the Court for sentence credit. The Defendant was sentenced as follows:
JAIL: 240 DAYS FIRST 14 DAYS TO BE SERVED AS STRAIGHT TIME FOLLOWED BY 226 DAYS WITH HUBER WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS. (sentence credit to be determined);
FINES AND COSTS PREVIOUSLY ORDERED BY THE COURT TO BE PAID AT $25.00 PER MONTH COMMENCING 10/1/17, 30 DAYS JAIL CONSECUTIVE AS PENALTY FOR NON PAYMENT.
